# State Transition Diagrams

## 1. Assignment Object

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Created
    Created --> Updated : Edit Assignment
    Created --> Completed : Mark Complete
    Created --> Deleted : Delete Assignment
    Updated --> Completed : Mark Complete
    Completed --> Archived

Explanation
It represents how an assignment moves from creation to completion or deletion.

stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Registered
    Registered --> Active : Login
    Active --> LoggedOut : Logout
    Active --> Suspended : Security Issue
    Suspended --> Active : Reactivate

Explanation
It shows lifecycle of a user account from registration to usage

stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Scheduled
    Scheduled --> Triggered : Time Reached
    Triggered --> Sent
    Sent --> Acknowledged

Explanation
It represents how reminders are scheduled and delivered.

stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> NotAuthenticated
    NotAuthenticated --> Authenticated : Login
    Authenticated --> Expired : Session Timeout
    Authenticated --> LoggedOut : Logout

It shows login session lifecycle.

stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Created
    Created --> Sent
    Sent --> Delivered
    Delivered --> Read

Represents how notifications are processed and consumed.

stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> NotStarted
    NotStarted --> InProgress
    InProgress --> Submitted
    Submitted --> Reviewed

Tracks assignment completion stages.

stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Pending
    Pending --> Running
    Running --> Completed
    Running --> Failed
    Failed --> Retried

Represents internal system operations like reminders.

